# Content & Data Rules

## data/ — static typed content

All copy and content lives in `data/*.ts`. **Never hard-code strings directly in JSX**.

```ts
// ✅ data/site.ts
export const HERO_VALUE_LINE = "Staff engineer focused on…";

// ❌ inline in component
<h1>Staff engineer focused on…</h1>
```

- Export constants in SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for copy strings.
- Export typed arrays/objects for structured data (experience, projects, skills).
- Do not add logic or side effects to data files — pure data only.

## content/ — Markdown blog posts

Posts use gray-matter frontmatter. Required fields:

```md
---
title: "Post title"
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
description: "One-sentence summary for SEO"
---
```

- Do not change existing post slugs (filename = URL slug).
- Load posts only through `utils/posts.ts` — never read Markdown files directly in components.
- Keep `data/posts/` index in sync when adding a new post.
